    <note type="biography">
        <p>American zoologist and missionary. Born and brought up in the Sandwich Islands (Hawaii). Educated partly in the United States. Missionary in Japan, 1862; China, 1863–75; Japan, 1876–99. Spent part of his furloughs in England. Studied organisms from the perspective of evolution and geographic distribution, paying especial attention to isolation.</p></note>
